  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e31" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Exemption from limitation on extension of certificate</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Section 31 (4) (a) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/18051" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Environmental Assessment Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, as it limits the number of times that a deadline specified in an environmental assessment certificate may be extended, does not apply in relation to the reviewable project described in Environmental Assessment Certificate # M09-02 if the deadline is not extended beyond January 14, 2022.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 2/2021.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/18051" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Environmental Assessment Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, S.B.C. 2018, c. 51, s. 77.]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
